s Stellet licht -- tCHAPTER TWELVE. CYCLICAL SCAPEGOATING: Inés de Oliveira Cézar’s Extranjera -- tCHAPTER THIRTEEN. THE IRREVOCABLE NATURE OF CURSES: Inés de Oliveira Cézar’s El recuento de los daños -- tCHAPTER FOURTEEN. SPLINTERED MIRRORS, ECHOES, AND REVERBERATIONS: Fernando Pérez Valdés’s Madrigal -- tPART SIX. EXPERIMENTAL PSEUDO-DOCUMENTARY -- tCHAPTER FIFTEEN. ROOM WITH A VIEW: Fernando Pérez Valdés’s Suite Habana -- tCHAPTER SIXTEEN. LIFE IS AND IS NOT: Paz Encina’s Hamaca paraguaya -- tCONCLUSION Possible Futures -- tNOTES -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhile there are numerous film studies that focus on one particular grouping of films—by nationality, by era, or by technique—here is the first single volume that incorporates all of the above, offering a broad overview of experimental Latin American film produced over the last twenty years. Analyzing seventeen recent films by eleven different filmmakers from Argentina, Brazil, Cuba, Mexico, Paraguay, and Peru, Cynthia Tompkins uses a comparative approach that finds commonalities among the disparate works in terms of their influences, aesthetics, and techniques. Tompkins introduces each film first in its sociohistorical context before summarizing it and then subverting its canonical interpretation. Pivotal to her close readings of the films and their convergences as a collective cinema is Tompkins’s application of Deleuzian film theory and the concept of the time-image as it pertains to the treatment of time and repetition. Tompkins also explores such topics as the theme of decolonization, the consistent use of montage, paratactically structured narratives, and the fusion of documentary conventions and neorealism with drama. An invaluable contribution to any dialogue on the avant-garde in general and to filmmaking both in and out of Latin America, Experimental Latin American Cinema is also a welcome and insightful addition to Latin American studies as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aExperimental filmszLatin AmericaxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/74415840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292744165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292744165/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK